            <title>[ENTESB-1421] KARAF Failover does not work after database  shutdown</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-1421</link>
                <project id="12314570" key="ENTESB">JBoss Fuse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Basically  they have 2 containers , configued use karaf failover according to &lt;a href=&quot;http://karaf.apache.org/manual/latest-2.3.x/users-guide/failover.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://karaf.apache.org/manual/latest-2.3.x/users-guide/failover.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;They used oracle JDBC lock, now both the master and slave are running.&lt;br/&gt;
Then the Database service was shutdown. They noticed that the master losed the lock as below, but now the slave can not acquire the lock too. when the database comes back again, they noticed that both slave and master can not acquire the lock. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;below is logs in master, I also attached the logs when I reproduce it .&lt;/p&gt;
